                    <li><%= link_to image_tag("carma/chocolate/small/Lifelongloveforchocolate-header.png", :class => "fboxImageSize"), "https://dqp5htr9jmxmj.cloudfront.net/assets/carma/chocolate/large/Lifelongloveforchocolate-header.jpg", :class => "fancybox", :rel => "gallery1", :title => "" %>
                    </li>
                    
                </ol>    
            </div>


            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    One of my favorite places for chocolate is in Rexburg, where I met a very good friend named Florence. She dipped chocolates in her kitchen, and it later became a business because it prospered for her. Florence’s Candy Kitchen in Rexburg is one of my favorite places.
            </span>
            
            <span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory1-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory1');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>

            <div id="restofstory1" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    One time last year, I believe it was at my birthday time, the girls, Debra and Janet, told me that on my birthday we were going to do something very special, but I was not to know where I was to go until we got there. They put me in the car, blindfolded me, and took me to Rexburg and down through the alley where Florence’s Candy Kitchen is. Then they took the blindfold off and there I was in her chocolate factory. She was very pleased and had agreed to show me through all the processes of making her wonderful chocolates. That was a special treat.<br /><br />

                    Another time, two years ago, my family on my birthday gave me a chocolate birthday party. They invited many people to come, family members, neighbors, whoever wanted to come; all they needed to do was bring something chocolate. We set up a big table in the sunroom and everyone that came put their chocolate on the table. When the social part of the party was over, everyone would help themselves to all the different kinds of chocolate. We had a chocolate fountain, we had chocolate milk, we had fudge, we had cherry chocolates…every kind that you could imagine. Everyone was privileged to take home a plate of chocolate. It was a really fun party, one I treasure.<br /><br />

                    I put together a scrapbook about all the fun things I’ve heard about chocolate and that people say about chocolate. I guess one of my favorite ones is “There’s no Chocoholics Anonymous because no one wants to quit eating chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    This little book I have is full of fun quotes. “When no one understands you, chocolate is always there.”<br /><br />

                    “Strength is the capacity to break a chocolate bar into four pieces with your bare hands and then eat just one of the pieces.” There’s so many fun things about chocolate!<br /><br />

                    I think most everyone likes chocolate. I don’t think I’ve ever met anyone who really didn’t like it—yes, I have met someone. My own daughter-in-law, Cyndi Bird, confessed to me one time, “I really don’t care for chocolate.” Our relationship was quite queasy then. I didn’t know how to accept that. My own daughter-in-law. But anyway, we still like each other.<br /><br />

                    Also, I have this theory that chocolate slows down the aging process. It may not be true, but dare I take the chance? And I’m pretty old, so I think it works. I think chocolate has done me good all my life. So there you have it.<br /><br />

                    I have an added thought to that. I have a P.S. I guess my love of chocolate is known world-wide, because a number of years ago, when Janet lived in England where Cadbury’s chocolate is made, she would send Cadbury’s chocolates back to me when she had the opportunity. If ever anybody went over there, she would always ask, “Mom, what do you want them to bring back to you? I don’t need to ask; I know it’s chocolate.” <br /><br />

                    One particular time she had a friend coming from over there. My favorites were the huge Cadbury bars that were about 18 inches long and about an inch thick. They were heavy, but she had a friend bring to me nine of those huge bars. He tied them up and he carried them on the plane from England and brought them and handed them to me. Those bars lasted a long time. They must have weighed a ton, but that sweet man carried them on the plane and brought them to me. <br /><br />

                    It’s kind of special liking chocolate that much.<br /><br />

                    I also collect quotes about chocolate. Here are a few: <br /><br />

                    “We must save planet earth...It’s the only one with chocolate!”<br /><br />

                    “If you’ve got chocolate all over your hands, you’re eating it too slowly!”<br /><br />

                    “CHOCOPHOBIA: The totally logical fear that the world will run out of chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    “After eating a bar of chocolate one can forgive anybody...even one’s relatives.”<br /><br />

                    “Chocolate never faileth.”<br /><br />

                    “Research tells us that fourteen out of any ten people like chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    “The 12 step chocoholics program: Rule #1 — Never ever be more than 12 steps away from chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    “When no one understands you… chocolate is there!”<br /><br />

                    “There is no chocoholics anonymous because no one wants to quit!”<br /><br />

                    “Chocolate is cheaper than therapy and you don’t need an appointment!”<br /><br />

                    “No day is so bad that it can’t be fixed with chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    “9 out of 10 people love chocolate. The 10th person lies.”<br /><br />

                    “And on the 8th day God created chocolate.”<br /><br />
                    
                    “All you need is love...and chocolate.”<br /><br />
                    
                    “Man cannot live by chocolate alone...but woman sure can!”<br /><br />
                    
                    “Exercise is a dirty word. Everytime I hear it, I wash out my mouth with chocolate.”<br /><br />
                    
                    “For some of us there’s therapy. For the rest of us there’s chocolate.”                  
                </span>

