            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                One of them is, “There’s a better way than the way of the world.” That’s a statement by Gordon B. Hinckley. <br /><br />

                Another is, “He who knows others is learned. He who knows himself is wise.” <br /><br />

                Oh, this is another one of my favorites. “God gave us memory that we might have roses in December.” <br /><br />

                I should sort these out first.
            </span>

            <span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory3-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory3');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>

            <div id="restofstory3" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    Oh, and this is another one of my favorites. “I’m stressed. I don’t know if I found a rope or lost my horse.”<br /><br />

                    “Judge not an eternal soul by the appearance of an earthly body.”<br /><br />

                    “The future is not something we enter. The future is something we create.”<br /><br />

                    “Sometimes we must be hurt in order to grow. Sometimes we must fail in order to know. Sometimes we must lose in order to gain, because some lessons in life are best learned through pain.”<br /><br />

                    “Life is what we make it. Always has been, always will.”<br /><br />

                    This is another favorite: “As long as you keep waking up in the morning is evidence that HE is not through with you.”<br /><br />

                    “Don’t compromise yourself. You’re all you’ve got.”<br /><br />

                    I need one that’s special. I need to find it.<br /><br />

                    “The main thing is to have the main thing be the main thing.”<br /><br />

                    “When life gives you lemons, throw ‘em back and demand chocolate.”<br /><br />

                    “We can’t all be heroes because someone has to sit on the curb and clap as they go by.”<br /><br />

                    “You were given this life because you’re strong enough to live it.”<br /><br />

                    These are all favorites!<br /><br />

                    “Good morning. Let the stress begin.”<br /><br />

                    “Be yourself. Just be yourself, because everyone else is taken.”<br /><br />

                    “While there are some things wrong in the world today, there are many things right, such as teachers who teach, ministers who minister, marriages that make it, parents who sacrifice, and friends who help.”<br /><br />

                    There are so many of these.<br /><br />

                    “If you see the light at the end of the tunnel, it’s the light of the oncoming train.”<br /><br />

                    “I believe everything happens for a reason. Usually the reason is somebody screwed up.”<br /><br />

                    There’s one I need to find here.<br /><br />

                    “A vacation is what you take when you can no longer take what you were taking.”<br /><br />

                    One favorite, I don’t think it’s written down here, but it says…I’ll have to find it.<br /><br />

                    “Be the kind of woman that when your feet touch the floor in the morning, the devil says, “Oh darn. She’s up!”<br /><br />

                    “I’m too blessed to be stressed.”<br /><br />

                    “When life does get tough and the crisis is undeniably at hand, we must in an instant look inward for strength of character to see us through. We will find nothing inside ourselves that we have not already put there.” That’s a good one.<br /><br />

                    “Practical guide for successful living: put your head under the pillow and scream.”<br /><br />

                    Oh, I’m taking too much time. <br /><br />

                    “Whether you think you can or think you can’t, you’re right.”<br /><br />

                    I like this one, too: “How beautiful it is to do nothing and then rest afterwards.”<br /><br />

                    “The power of the Book of Mormon is the application of the doctrine therein.”<br /><br />

                    This is a statement by President Harold B. Lee: “I bear you my witness that the Savior is closer to us than you have any idea. He will be closer to you and powers divine will be at your side when you have nowhere else to turn.”<br /><br />

                    I should have sorted these out ahead of time.<br /><br />

                    “Do not spoil what you have by desiring what you have not, but remember that what you have now was among the things you hoped for.”<br /><br />

                    Oh, this one is a special favorite by President Gordon B. Hinckley: “Anyone who imagines that bliss is normal is going to waste a lot of time running around shouting that he’s been robbed. The fact is that most putts don’t drop. Most beef is tough. Most children grow up to be just people. Most successful marriages require a high degree of mutual toleration. Most jobs are more often dull than otherwise. The trick is to thank the Lord for letting you have the ride.”<br /><br />
                </span>

