            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                The home was on seven acres. There are two acres of woods, two acres of pastures, and then an acre and a half for the home. I’m not sure just what the numbers are.<br /><br />

                After we had lived here for a number of years, we found that the family loved to come here. They often planned their summer vacations to come, and eventually we had family reunions. I'm not sure just which year we started; I think it was about 1989. The family loved to come especially for reunions. We managed to put everyone up, and they loved to be together. They looked forward to coming and we looked forward so much to having them come. To be together, to show the love we feel for each other, and to see the cooperation—it was just full of love! The reunions have been wonderful. 
