            <div id="restofstory5" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    We always had a theme for our reunions, and everyone in the family participated. We had committees. Everyone was part of a committee, preparing meals and preparing games to play. The food was a big deal. We always tried to have special food that everyone would enjoy. We often had the food catered, but mostly family wanted to work together, to be together, and to have fun together. Our family has always had those blessings of enjoying being together and looking forward to reunion time. We had about half a dozen reunions here in this home. <br /><br />

                    I think reunions are a very special part of family relationships. They bring families together; for those who’ve lived far away and been separated for a number of years, when they come to a reunion—I don't know how to describe it. It's such a warm, special time to be together with those that you love and be part of a very special family. We have always enjoyed having the reunions.<br /><br />

                    <div class="vidvid"><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/122470506" width="500" height="375" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></div><br />

                    The last one we had here had about eighty-five people. It was a riot! A riot. Everyone loved it. We had barrels of fun. We were together for about four days total. Some even wanted to stay longer. Family from Mesa traveled so far and they wanted to come and stay longer, so of course we welcomed that. It's a special feeling to know that your family wants to come back home and to be with you—very special.<br /><br />

                    Cyndi gave me a kitchen towel, and the last reunion she hung it on my oven door and I didn't know who left it there. But the towel explains a family. I believe the towel says, “Home is where Mom is.” That's kind of what family is. We don't have a dad right now, but home is where Mom and Dad are, wherever they live. That's where home is. <br /><br />

                    We've always been a close family. We've always enjoyed being close together. We've had many, many blessings in our family because of our love of the gospel, our desire to be together, and the love we feel for one another.
